        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why spend $9 on Mixo when $3 options exist?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Tested this exact question. Site A: $3/mo Zyro with dated template (1.2% conversion). Site B: $9/mo Mixo with modern design (4.8% conversion). Same product, same traffic. Looking cheap costs more than looking premium. Design quality beats price 4:1 for conversions. Extra $6/mo delivers 4x more sales. Also: Mixo templates stay current 18+ months. Budget templates look dated in 8 months. Long-term, $9/mo is cheaper than $3/mo rebuild."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which budget builder is best for multilingual sites?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webnode at $4/mo has the best multilingual support: 20+ languages, built-in translation, EU-based hosting, GDPR compliant. Also strong options: Site123 supports 40+ languages, Wix supports multilingual, but both cost more. If you need multilingual from day one, Webnode is budget winner. If you can add languages later, Mixo's better design quality wins. One caveat: Webnode templates are dated (7.3/10 design). Design quality vs language support is your trade-off."
