          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, budget builders can hurt SEO in three ways: (1) PageSpeed - Site123 scores 40-50 on mobile, Framer scores 90+. Google penalizes slow sites. (2) Templates - Budget templates look dated, users bounce (80%+ bounce rate = low rankings). (3) Features - Budget builders lack advanced SEO tools (schema, sitemaps, canonical tags). Mixo at $9/mo includes these. For SEO, spend the extra $6. Better PageSpeed, better templates, better tools = better rankings. One client moved from Site123 to Mixo: organic traffic increased 3.2x in 90 days."
        }
      },
